PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780697476
OL,3,CAndy Burnham confirms he would run in
OL,4,Crace to replace Keir Starmer
OL,6,FEven if Burnham does not win the by-
OL,7,Felection, it is likely Starmer will
OL,8,Fface a leadership challenge, with both
OL,9,Fformer deputy prime minister Angela
OL,10,FRayner and Streeting thought to be
OL,11,Fconsidering their chances.
OL,13,FThe vote is expected to be a race
OL,14,Fbetween Burnham and Reform UK's
OL,15,Fcandidate, Robert Kenyon, a plumber
OL,16,Fand local councillor.
OL,18,FKenyon has faced criticism over past
OL,19,Fsocial media comments unearthed by
OL,20,Fseveral newspapers, including his
OL,21,Fstance towards Brexit and abortion.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
